{"key":"processedPost-8879738","value":{"id":8879738,"first":8879267,"last":8882403,"when":1220587762,"utime":"09/05/08 07:09 AM","content":"Actually, humidity doesn't 'fall'.&nbsp; My greenhouses are always higher humidity on the upper shelves than on the lower ones.<br /><br />A cool mist works by shooting a fine mist straight up into the air.&nbsp; For this reason, the humidifier should be on the floor of the greenhouse, with nothing above.&nbsp; If the mist hits a shelf above, the stream will condense and drip back down, making a mess on the floor.<br /><br />I'd put the cool mist on the floor of one side of your greenhouse, making sure the mist(you can see it) goes straight up without hitting walls or shelves.&nbsp; This will not only give the most humidity, but it will circulate the air inside the greenhouse.&nbsp; If you'll cut windows and slits in the plastic, the circulating air will cause fresh air to be drawn in through the openings.<br />RR","title":"Re: Importance of humidifier placement..."}}